</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[805,1406,1287,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
In describing 
<taxonomicName authority=", Miller (1768)" authorityName=", Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[1001,1405,1521,1547]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">
<emphasis box="[1001,1238,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Solanum fruticosum,</emphasis>
Miller (1768)
</taxonomicName>
cited “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[879,1100,1554,1580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">Solanum fruticosum</taxonomicName>
bacciferum, spinosum, flore caeruleo Sl. C. 108
</emphasis>
” and made reference to the collector William Houstoun. The specimen selected here as the lectotype for this name in BM is annotated with the same reference to Sloane, and bears a label in Houstoun’s hand (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1092,1721,1747]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[181,215,1800,1821]" captionTargetBox="[181,1435,585,1771]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Solanum bahamense L. a, Lectotype of S. fruticosum Mill., Houstoun s.n. (BM000815974); b, lectotype of S. varginstonicum Buc’hoz, Buc’hoz, Pl. Nouv. Découv. 48., t. 46, 1784. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; c, lectotype of Solanum persicifolium Dunal, Plumier,Plant. Amer. t. 245, f. 2, 1763. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; d, lectotype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal, Sloane, Voy. Jamaica t. 145, fig. 3, 1707. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; e, epitype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal (BM000589942). Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum,London;f, lectotype of S. persicifolium var.belloi O.E.Schulz,Heller 4605 (F-80757). Reproduced with permission of the Field Museum of Natural History." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326310/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). It is also a good match for the description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[805,1406,1287,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buc’hoz" box="[833,1108,1788,1814]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="varginstonicum">
<emphasis box="[833,1108,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Solanum varginstonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was named by Buc’hoz in honour of George Washington, with a spectacular misspelling of the name. No specimens have been traced for Buc’hoz’s names, so the plate (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1337,1888,1914]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[181,215,1800,1821]" captionTargetBox="[181,1435,585,1771]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Solanum bahamense L. a, Lectotype of S. fruticosum Mill., Houstoun s.n. (BM000815974); b, lectotype of S. varginstonicum Buc’hoz, Buc’hoz, Pl. Nouv. Découv. 48., t. 46, 1784. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; c, lectotype of Solanum persicifolium Dunal, Plumier,Plant. Amer. t. 245, f. 2, 1763. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; d, lectotype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal, Sloane, Voy. Jamaica t. 145, fig. 3, 1707. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; e, epitype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal (BM000589942). Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum,London;f, lectotype of S. persicifolium var.belloi O.E.Schulz,Heller 4605 (F-80757). Reproduced with permission of the Field Museum of Natural History." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326310/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
) is selected here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[805,1406,1287,1981]" lastBlockId="5.[835,1436,207,507]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
In his description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Dunal (1813)" authorityName=", Dunal" authorityYear="1813" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="70" order="Solanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persicifolium">
<emphasis box="[1073,1327,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Solanum persicifolium,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dunal, M. - F." journalOrPublisher="Montpellier" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" refId="ref13588" refString="Dunal, M. - F. 1813. Histoire naturelle, medicale et economique des Solanum et des genres qui ont ete confundus avec eux. Montpellier." title="Histoire naturelle, medicale et economique des Solanum et des genres qui ont ete confundus avec eux" type="book" year="1813">Dunal (1813)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cites two pre-Linnean sources; 
<bibRefCitation author="Plumier, C." journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" refId="ref14369" refString="Plumier, C. 1703. Nova plantarum Americanarum genera. Paris." title="Nova plantarum Americanarum genera" type="book" year="1703">Plumier’s (1703)</bibRefCitation>
catalogue (“Plumier cat. 4”) bound with the 
<emphasis box="[181,542,275,301]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Nova Plantarum Americanarum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Plumier, C." box="[559,722,275,301]" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" refId="ref14369" refString="Plumier, C. 1703. Nova plantarum Americanarum genera. Paris." title="Nova plantarum Americanarum genera" type="book" year="1703">Plumier, 1703</bibRefCitation>
) and the larger compilation of Plumier’s American plants illustrated by Johannes Burman from tracings of Plumier’s originals held in Paris (“Burm., Plant. Amer. p. 240, t. 244, fig. 2”; Plumier, 1755-1760, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jarvis, C." box="[181,315,447,473]" journalOrPublisher="Linnean Society of London and the Natural History Museum, London" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" refId="ref13969" refString="Jarvis, C. 2007. Order out of chaos: Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London and the Natural History Museum, London." title="Order out of chaos: Linnaean plant names and their types" type="book" year="2007">Jarvis, 2007</bibRefCitation>
for a discussion of Plumier’s plates). On page 4 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Plumier, C." box="[294,463,481,507]" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" refId="ref14369" refString="Plumier, C. 1703. Nova plantarum Americanarum genera. Paris." title="Nova plantarum Americanarum genera" type="book" year="1703">Plumier’s 1703</bibRefCitation>
catalogue is the polynomial “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[845,1080,207,233]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticosum">Solanum fruticosum</taxonomicName>
, persicae foliis, 
<taxonomicName box="[1253,1376,207,233]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatum">aculeatum</taxonomicName>
”; this same polynomial is associated with plate 244 in the illustrated edition (
<bibRefCitation author="Plumier, C." box="[1043,1211,275,301]" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" refId="ref14382" refString="Plumier, C. 1757. Plantarum Americanarum fasciculus primus (… decimus) continens plantas quas olim Carolus Plumierus .. depinxit has edidit … Johannes Burman. Amsterdam." title="Plantarum Americanarum fasciculus primus (… decimus) continens plantas quas olim Carolus Plumierus .. depinxit has edidit … Johannes Burman" type="book" year="1757">Plumier, 1757</bibRefCitation>
). In the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dunal, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Dunal" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Prodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,275,301]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Prodromus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dunal, M. - F." box="[843,988,310,336]" editor="A. P. de Candolle" journalOrPublisher="Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 690" part="13" refId="ref13664" refString="Dunal, M. - F. 1852. Solanaceae. In: A. P. de Candolle (ed.), Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 13 (1): 1 - 690." title="Solanaceae" type="journal article" year="1852">Dunal, 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, Dunal cites several specimens, stating that the Burman plate was “mala”. The Burman plate, however, is the only verifiable element associated with the original description (although Dunal may have seen the originals in Paris) and is thus here selected as the lectotype (
<figureCitation box="[995,1073,481,507]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[181,215,1800,1821]" captionTargetBox="[181,1435,585,1771]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Solanum bahamense L. a, Lectotype of S. fruticosum Mill., Houstoun s.n. (BM000815974); b, lectotype of S. varginstonicum Buc’hoz, Buc’hoz, Pl. Nouv. Découv. 48., t. 46, 1784. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; c, lectotype of Solanum persicifolium Dunal, Plumier,Plant. Amer. t. 245, f. 2, 1763. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; d, lectotype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal, Sloane, Voy. Jamaica t. 145, fig. 3, 1707. Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum Botany Library; e, epitype of S. bahamense var. lanceolatum Dunal (BM000589942). Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum,London;f, lectotype of S. persicifolium var.belloi O.E.Schulz,Heller 4605 (F-80757). Reproduced with permission of the Field Museum of Natural History." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
